      section
        h2 Parameters and scopes
        h3 The parameters to a function behave like regular variables, but their initial values are given by the caller of the function
        
      
      section 
        h2 Scopes
        h3 An important property of functions is that the variables created inside of them, including their parameters, are local to the function. 
        pre
          code.language-javascript.

            var x = "outside";

            var f1 = function() {
              var x = "inside f1";
            };
            
            f1();
            
            console.log(x);
            // → outside

            var f2 = function() {
              x = "inside f2";
            };
            f2();
            console.log(x);
            // → inside f2
        
      
